notes: Shahid Afridi acted as a runner for Saeed Anwar starting from 18.6 over, until the end.
Pakistan innings: 1x7 ball over (37th over - Kumble's 6th over)
Pakistan innings: 1x5 ball over (49th over - Tendulkar's 9th over). Both allowed by umpire Francis.
Saeed Anwar breaks the previous record for the highest innings in one-day internationals (189, IVA Richards v England, 1984).
Mohammad Wasim substituted for Saeed Anwar throughout the Indian innings.
Tendulkar acted as runner for Dravid during overs 23 and 24.

milestones.description: Saeed Anwar has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (118) in an innings in ODIs for PAK, going past Shahid Afridi's 90
Saeed Anwar's 194 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for PAK), surpassing Inzamam-ul-Haq's 137
This is the highest match aggregate (619) involving teams India & Pakistan in ODIs
Saeed Anwar has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (118) in an innings in ODIs, going past Viv Richards's 114
